Package org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.opt

Class SchematicSimulation2

java.lang.Object
org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.opt.AbstractSimulation2
org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.opt.SchematicSimulation2
All Implemented Interfaces:
Simulation2
public class SchematicSimulation2
extends AbstractSimulation2
This class provides an implementation of the procedure SchematicSimilarity1 in [Monika Rauch Henzinger, Thomas A. Henzinger, Peter W. Kopke: Computing Simulations on Finite and Infinite Graphs. FOCS 1995: 453-462] for computing the simulation relations between two automata. Note that the alphabets of the input automata must be the same and non-empty.
Author:
Ming-Hsien Tsai

  • Constructor Details

    • SchematicSimulation2

      public SchematicSimulation2​(FSA aut1, FSA aut2)
      Constructs this object to compute the simulation relation between two automata. The two automata are assumed to have the same label position, the same alphabet type, and the same acceptance condition. The fair simulation is considered.
      Parameters:
      aut1 - an automaton
      aut2 - an automaton

    • SchematicSimulation2

      public SchematicSimulation2​(FSA aut1, FSA aut2, boolean fair)
      Constructs this object to compute the simulation relation between two automata. The two automata are assumed to have the same label position, the same alphabet type, and the same acceptance condition.
      Parameters:
      aut1 - an automaton
      aut2 - an automaton
      fair - indicating if the fair simulation should be considered
